table_caption: Physical, cooking, and eating quality indicators of rice samples obtained from respondents by income class.
table_foot: a Figures presented here are means and standard deviations (in parentheses). For peak time, a different lowercase letter beside each mean indicates that the means are significantly different (α = 0.05).b The conversion rate at the time of the study (November 2012) was 1 USD = 41.12 PHP.c The letter beside the p-value indicates the test statistic used: (A) ANOVA (F-statistic), (B) Kruskal-Wallis rank sum test (χ2).
